$ SQL*Plus: SET DEFINE
@ set define

`set define` sets the character that indicates → development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus/_variables#sql-plus-substitution-var[substitution variables] by prefixing them with this character
code {
set define !

→ development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus/define var=42
→ development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus/define tab=→ development/databases/Oracle/SQL/dual

→ development/databases/Oracle/SQL/select !var num from !tab;
code }

Variable substitution can be turned of with
code {
set define off
code }

The default character is the ampersand (`&`).

sa:

  Using `→ development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus/define` to assign a value to a → development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus/_variables[variable].

  → development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus/_variables#sql-plus-substitution-var[Substitution variables]

 `→ development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus/set/escape`

  → development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus
